From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 14 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] xxd: remove redundant K&R extern declarations for strtol/ftell

GCC 15 defaults to C23, where an empty parameter list () means the
function takes no arguments. The old K&R-style declarations:

  extern long int strtol();
  extern long int ftell();

are therefore interpreted as "takes no arguments", conflicting with
every call site that passes arguments. Both functions are already
properly declared via the included <stdlib.h> and <stdio.h>; remove
the redundant extern lines.
---
 xxd.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/xxd.c b/xxd.c
--- a/xxd.c
+++ b/xxd.c
@@ -142,4 +142,2 @@
-extern long int strtol();
-extern long int ftell();
-
 char version[] = "xxd v1.11, 8 jun 2013 by Juergen Weigert et al.";
